	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think the 40KB one is just the standard dump padded or mirrored to fill the space.  If it has CHR-ROM, then it's just probably a copy of the CHR-RAM contents that the BIOS writes there.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


