		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Does the BIOS copy its own code to RAM or something?</div><br />No, it only copies things to VRAM.<br /><br />However as far I know I think the BIOS is embedded on an ASIC chip (as opposed to being it's own 8kb ROM chip) which makes it especially difficult to dump. Myself I couldn't even open my RAM adapter without fearing to do irreversible damage to it... pehaps if I ever gets my hands on a second RAM adapter I could open it and observe it (they are cheap since there is so many broken FDS drives, and this makes the adapter alone completely useless).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


