	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As far as &quot;works&quot; goes, Bizhawk, when fed a 40976 byte supposed bios, will extract the appropriate 8k from it and use that as its FDS bios.  Perhaps other emulators do this as well?  Also, if you try to load the 40976 byte bios as an iNES, it should run in most emulators:  the bios splash screen will be shown, but nothing else will happen, if it's emulated as NROM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


